High Priority - Core Navigation Features
Priority	Feature	Description
1	GPS Position & Tracking	Show user's position, heading, speed on chart; follow mode
2	Route Planning	Create waypoints, routes, measure distance/bearing
3	Search	Find places by name (leverage GNIS data), find chart features
4	Offline Base Maps	Cache Mapbox tiles for fully offline operation
Medium Priority - Data & Coverage
Priority	Feature	Description
5	Expand Chart Coverage	Add more Alaska regions, Pacific Northwest, etc.
6	Tide Stations	Show tide predictions at NOAA tide stations
7	Current Data	Display tidal current predictions
8	Weather Overlay	NOAA marine weather, wind, waves
Lower Priority - Polish & Infrastructure
Priority	Feature	Description
9	Firebase Cloud Sync	Download charts from cloud instead of manual push
10	Automatic NOAA Updates	Check for and apply chart updates
11	Night Mode	Red-tinted display for night bridge use
12	Bookmarks/Favorites	Save locations for quick access
13	iOS Build & Testing	Test and deploy on iOS


 Data Layers to Add
Priority	Layer	Data Source	Description
1	Tide Stations	NOAA CO-OPS	Show tide station locations with predictions
2	Current Stations	NOAA CO-OPS	Tidal current predictions at stations
3	Weather Buoys	NDBC	Real-time wind, waves, temperature
4	AIS Vessel Traffic	AIS feeds	Live ship positions (requires data subscription)
5	Traffic Separation Schemes	S-57 TSSLPT/TSEZNE	Shipping lanes already in ENC data
6	Ice Coverage	NWS/NIC	Sea ice extent (important for Alaska)
7	Marine Sanctuaries	NOAA	National marine sanctuary boundaries
8	Fishing Closures	NOAA Fisheries	Seasonal/area fishing restrictions
S-57 Layers Not Yet Displayed
These are already in the ENC data but not rendered:
Layer	S-57 Code	Description
Fog Signals	FOGSIG	Fog horns, bells, whistles
Pilot Boarding	PILBOP	Pilot pickup areas
Recommended Tracks	RECTRC	Suggested navigation routes
Two-Way Routes	TWRTPT	Traffic separation
Offshore Platforms	OFSPLF	Oil rigs, platforms
Mooring Facilities	MORFAC	Mooring buoys, dolphins

